  "response_text": "I'll explain the causes of tides, rating my confidence level for each step and noting any gaps in the model.\n\n**Step 1: Gravitational Force of the Moon (Confidence: 9/10)**\nThe primary cause of tides is the gravitational force exerted by the Moon on the Earth's oceans. The Moon's gravity pulls on the water molecules in the ocean, creating a bulge in the water. This bulge is what we experience as a high tide.\n\n**Step 2: Gravitational Force of the Sun (Confidence: 8.5/10)**\nThe Sun also exerts a gravitational force on the Earth's oceans, although it's much weaker than the Moon's. However, when the Sun and Moon are aligned (at new moon or full moon), their gravitational forces work together to create even higher high tides and lower low tides, known as spring tides. When the Sun and Moon are at right angles to each",
